        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1059063911" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11271583293686050335">This book is definitely a hard one to review! It is most definitely not light reading, but deals with a lot of hard hitting subjects that are difficult at best to deal with in one&apos;s life. It is a very emotional read, allowing us to forge a deep connection to the characters, and yet I kept feeling like something was missing from the story. Some events happened too fast for my liking, and I also didn&apos;t agree with how things ended up between certain characters. The religious theme in the book is ve</span>
  <span id="freeText11271583293686050335" style="display:none">This book is definitely a hard one to review! It is most definitely not light reading, but deals with a lot of hard hitting subjects that are difficult at best to deal with in one's life. It is a very emotional read, allowing us to forge a deep connection to the characters, and yet I kept feeling like something was missing from the story. Some events happened too fast for my liking, and I also didn't agree with how things ended up between certain characters. The religious theme in the book is very heavy handed, almost preachy to a degree, and woven throughout the story, but was essential to how the story turned out. I'm not entirely sure I liked it all that well, and am hesitant to read the sequel to this or the rest of the series.</span>
